## {{ rule.title }}

[26 U.S.C. § 1411](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1411&num=0&edition=prelim) imposes a 3.8 % surtax on the lesser of *net investment income* and the excess of *modified AGI* over the filing-status threshold (`$200,000` single, `$250,000` joint, `$125,000` MFS). NIIT is a **separate additional tax** — the foreign tax credit and treaty re-sourcing credit do **not** offset it. The [Form 8960](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-8960) worksheet computes it; the result hits Schedule 2 line 12.

{% set niit = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
For 2025:

- AGI / modified AGI from US25-07: **{{ rule.inputs_by_key["us.stage.adjusted_gross_income"].value | money(currency="USD") }}**
- [§ 1411](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1411&num=0&edition=prelim) threshold for your filing status (US25-00 already validated this): the engine uses **{{ niit.modified_agi_excess_usd | money(currency="USD") }}** as the modified-AGI excess (`max(0, modified_AGI − threshold)`).
- Net investment income (dividends + interest + net capital gain + Schedule 1 substitute payments + staking, per your election): **{{ niit.net_investment_income_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- NIIT base (lesser of net investment income and modified-AGI excess): **{{ niit.niit_base_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- **NIIT = 3.8 % × base = {{ niit.niit_usd | money(currency="USD") }}** — Schedule 2 line 12 / [Form 8960](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-8960) line 17.

NIIT is added on top of regular tax (after FTC) when computing total liability at US25-21.

